post.description:
Admin Restricted

A Venue is an entity that provides the physical or virtual location of an Event. An Event has an associated sibling Venue.

Venues are not restricted by Group nor Event.

Venue name describes the location. Ex: “Joe’s Diner” and the Venue’s location property supports metadata about the Venue relevent for Users.

Example Venue Object:

{
    "url": null,
    "name": "Saint Frank Inner Sunset",
    "location": {
        "applePlaceID": "ABC123456",
        "title": "Irving at 9th Ave",
        "longitude": -122.466,
        "latitude": 37.7643
    },
    "id": "CFDA3654-4E40-4E39-BCCA-8C98E7131883"
}

For this example, the Web UI shows:

“Saint Frank Inner Sunset”
“Irving at 9th Ave”

with a link similar to:

https://maps.apple.com/place?name=Irving%20at%209th%20Ave&coordinate=37.7643,-122.466

post.description:
Admin Restricted

Allows an Admin to upload media such as an image or video.

Uploads are “streamed” in the sense that the server reads bytes as the come in. The entire upload must complete or the server will return an error and the media will not be written to the database.

The only useful reason to do this is to associate the media with a Group or Event’s imageURL property.
